A higher stamp tax will be levied on foreign buyers when acquiring properties in the UK
The Conservative Party has announced plans to levy a higher stamp tax on foreign buyers acquiring property in the UK, with the additional revenue to be invested in aid to homeless people.
The move will neutralize the success of Corbyn’s campaign to attract the youngest electorate
The increase in the stamp tax will affect buyers who are not taxed in the UK
The Ministry of Finance hopes to raise up to <0xC2><0xA3>120 million a year to help the homeless
